Use the standard library
This is how to parse_nested_parens of paren_string:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that depth is 0
   Remember that best is 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this paren_string's length times:
      Remember that c is item i in paren_string
      When c is 40, then:
         Increase depth
         When depth is more than best, then:
            Remember that best is depth
         End when
      End when
      When c is 41, then:
         Decrease depth
         When depth is 0, then:
            Add result to best
            Remember that best is 0
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> parse_nested_parens of "(()()) ((())) () ((())()())"
[2, 3, 1, 3]
>>> parse_nested_parens of "() (()) ((())) (((())))"
[1, 2, 3, 4]